cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.CC

This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning, specifically focusing on type-logical grammars and their practical applicability. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves the implementation of an algorithm and experiments, which suggests that it could also fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper deals with data-driven lexical types, which could place it under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper involves parsing and resolving structural ambiguities, which could also place it under cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
